<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_(8482057992).jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg/220px-I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="113" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg/330px-I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg/440px-I9_18satamana_TaxilaGandhara_1ar_%288482057992%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2496" data-file-height="1281" /></a><figcaption>A monetary silver coin of the satrapy of Gandhara about 500–400 BC. <b>Obv:</b> Gandhara symbol representing 6 weapons with one point between two weapons; At the bottom of the point, a hollow moon. <b>Rev:</b> Empty. <b>Dimensions:</b> 14 mm <b>Weight:</b> 1.4 g.</figcaption></figure>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Gandarans_in_Achaemenid_Army">Gandarans in Achaemenid Army</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gand%C4%81ra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Gandarans in Achaemenid Army"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><p>
According to <a href="/wiki/Herodotus" title="Herodotus">Herodotus</a>, soldiers of Gandāra participated to the <a href="/wiki/Second_Persian_invasion_of_Greece" title="Second Persian invasion of Greece">Second Persian invasion of Greece</a> around 480 BC.<sup id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-18">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> They had a different equipment from the <a href="/wiki/Hindush" title="Hindush">Hindush</a>, rather akin to that of the Bactrians, and were under the command of <a href="/wiki/Artyphius" title="Artyphius">Artyphius</a>, son of <a href="/wiki/Artabanus_(son_of_Hystaspes)" title="Artabanus (son of Hystaspes)">Artabanus</a>:<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1211633275">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 32px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style></p><blockquote class="templatequote"><p><small>The Bactrians in the army wore a headgear most like to the Median, carrying their native bows of reed, and short spears. (...) The Parthians, Chorasmians, Sogdians, Gandarians, and Dadicae in the army had the same equipment as the Bactrians. The Parthians and Chorasmians had for their commander <a href="/wiki/Artabazos_I_of_Phrygia" title="Artabazos I of Phrygia">Artabazus son of Pharnaces</a>, the Sogdians Azanes son of Artaeus, the Gandarians and Dadicae <a href="/wiki/Artyphius" title="Artyphius">Artyphius</a> son of <a href="/wiki/Artabanus_(son_of_Hystaspes)" title="Artabanus (son of Hystaspes)">Artabanus</a>.</small></p><div class="templatequotecite">—&#8202;<cite>Herodotus <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Herodotus/7B*.html">VII 64-66</a></cite></div></blockquote>
<p>The depiction of Indian soldiers and the names of the three <a href="/wiki/Ancient_India" class="mw-redirect" title="Ancient India">Ancient Indian</a> provinces including Gandāra still appear in trilingual cuneiform labels above their respective figures on the tomb of <a href="/wiki/Artaxerxes_II" title="Artaxerxes II">Artaxerxes II</a> (c.358 BC).<sup id="cite_ref-Olmstead,_History_of_the_Persian_Empire_1948_291–292_19-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Olmstead,_History_of_the_Persian_Empire_1948_291–292-19">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Inscription_A2Pa_of_Artaxerxes_II_20-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Inscription_A2Pa_of_Artaxerxes_II-20">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-PL271_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PL271-21">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gand%C4%81ra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: See also"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/India_(Herodotus)" title="India (Herodotus)">India (Herodotus)</a></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gand%C4%81ra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
